<br>
I'll argue that TWC, who commonly raids for 10-12 hour sessions (sometimes not even ending before people are eating breakfast) is more hardcore than HnE and their 4 hour raid days.  Whether I am right or wrong is not significant (and I can already think of several counter-arguments), the point is that it is possible to seperate 'hardcore' from 'progress.' <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=205399"><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://mywebpages.comcast.net/vicour1/NandSig.gif" style="border:0;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
